JDBC
Java Database Connectivity
- Comes with JDK, work with relational database system
- it is under java.sql package => import java.sql.*;
- it has set of Interfaces and classes to work with and RDMS

"jdbc:oracle:thin:@ec2-54-159-174-62.compute-1.amazonaws.com:1521:XE"

jdbc : connection using java
oracle: database vendor :RDMS
IP_ADDRESS -- HOSTNAME or IP
1521 -- PORT USED FOR ORACLE DATABASE == POSTGRES 5322 MYSQL 3306
XE -- sid number unique identifier for oracle db

3 Important Interfaces in JDBC

Connection
Statement
ResultSet


getString(columnIndex)
getString(ColumnName)

getInt
getDouble
getDate